overview: The user initiated a planning phase for a "Sleep Questionnaire
  Application" based on a provided Statement of Work. The primary intent was to
  assess the current codebase and outline the remaining tasks, specifically
  focusing on database implementation for questionnaire responses, a
  client-facing dashboard for data access, and any required authentication
  middleware. The evaluation revealed that while core questionnaire components
  and PDF generation are present, the application lacks a database schema for
  storing questionnaire responses, an API for CSV data retrieval, a user
  interface for a client dashboard, and an authentication system to secure it.
  The plan will need to address these missing components to fulfill the SOW
  requirements.
